\par <#/>But whether they were bought or not was not what concerned the couple.
\par <#/>"We just hope that they will return the children to us," Mutungu said. <#/>"Life is so empty without them here and you see it was not our fault that we do not have children of our own," he said emotionally.
\par <X_>}{\v\fs24\lang2057 <#/>It was clear he and his wife had brought up the children as their own and had grown to love them dearly.
\par }\pard\plain \s43\qj\nowidctlpar\adjustright \lang2057 {\v <#/>He however said they only had three and that the fourth child belonged to a woman from Kakamega who had left the child there while attending to a few chores.
\par <#/>Sources revealed that the youngest of the children had also been brought from Kakamega and was due for sale to a childless woman. <#/>But the latter contested
 the cost of the deal, hence the leakage to the police. <#/>She is said to have contested the exorbitant price which the seller demanded. <#/><-/They> latter asked for Sh5,000 while the <-/Muchungu> couple had paid Sh2,000 for each child.
\par }\pard\plain \qj\nowidctlpar\adjustright \fs20\lang1031 {\v <#/>}{\v\fs24\lang2057 Two days later, when the }{\i\v\fs24\lang2057 Nation}{\v\fs24\lang2057  revisited the home, the children had been returned.
\par <#/>But on seeing the car, the children suddenly broke into mourning for fear that they would be taken away. <#/>"<ea_>}{\i\v\fs24\lang2057 Ndirenda gukuo<ea/>"}{\v\fs24\lang2057  (I don't want to be carried), young George screamed as he ran away from us.

\par <#/>He was not to return until we departed.
\par <#/>Our investigations revealed that the four children are victims of a custom that used to be practised by most African communities in the past but which still thrives strongly in the Luhya community of western Kenya.
\par <#/>The children are said to have been born of incestuous relationships or between relatives. <#/>But the Luhya custom dictates that any such child is a bad omen and should be done away with. <#/>In some clans, they we
re even left to die soon after they were born.
